      "message": "This is not about user time zone change. This is about automatic time zone resolve. \"DISABLED\" means that automatic time zone resolve is disabled (i.e. policy prohibits time zone resolve).\n\nIP_ONLY / SEND_WIFI_ACCESS_POINTS / SEND_ALL_LOCATION_INFO - this are different levels of location resolve precision, allowing to send either no (IP_ONLY), WiFi of all environment information to Google Geolocation API. So these three actually allow automatic time zone resolve.\n\nBut TimezonePrefsManaged(prefs::kUserTimezone) is designed to enable/disable user time zone UI controls. This way policy may prevent user from modifying time zone manually, at the same time either turning on of off automatic time zone detection.",
